Description: Fragment of sub-round handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join to sharpish turn. Clay fine pink-buff. Rectangular stamp with winged caduceus symbol.
Curator's comments: Name Eukleitos. Trimmed. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC ABC 0350.05.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0954)
